  "bookTitle": "Rabbit Ranger",
  "bookId": 51,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A famous phantom thief ninja in the city. Despite having a conspicuous pair of rabbit ears, she can slip into any room unnoticed.",
  "personality": "An optimistic thief who believes in honor among thieves. She only steals from the wealthy and shares with the poor.",
  "like": "Vegetable crackers, ninja tools, panties",
  "familiarData": "Didian is a highly agile rabbit-kin girl who runs fast and can leap to heights silently. No matter how high the window, it becomes her entry point.\nShe claims to use ninjutsu, but ninjas use kunai, not forks. Yet despite seeming like a joke weapon, the fork is an all-purpose tool - whether picking locks, climbing walls, stealing, or even fighting, everything can be done with a fork. A real ninja would call it unbelievable.\n\nDidian is a righteous thief who only steals from the rich and shares most of it with the poor. Her beneficiaries are of all races, so many people are grateful to her and help hide her tracks, making it impossible for guards to catch her.\nIn truth, many guards are fans of this cute rabbit-kin girl, cheering for her thefts from goblins. Many guards look the other way when she steals, and they even greet each other when they cross paths.\n\nShe is sworn sisters with the wandering knight Mier, and is registered with the knight order, nominally making her a knight as well. The two once joined forces to defeat a slave hunter group a hundred strong.",
